<!--A special feature in Western Yugur is the occurrence of [[preaspiration|preaspiration]], corresponding to the so-called [[pharyngealisation|pharyngealised]] or low [[vowel|vowel]]s in [[Tuvan_language|Tuva]] and Tofa, and [[short_vowel|short vowel]]s in [[Yakut_language|Yakut]] and [[Turkmen_language|Turkmen]].  Examples of this phenomenon include {{IPA|/oʰtɯs/}} "thirty", {{IPA|/jaʰʂ/}} "good", and {{IPA|/iʰt/}} "meat".

